      <hedline>
        <hl1>Facing the Threat of a Nuclear Iran</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tom Collier letter asks whether US should expect Iran, under threat, to invite US to tea and nice talk about its nuclear ambitions</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Let's not kid ourselves,'' you say (''Recipe for a Perfect Crisis,'' editorial, April 15). O.K., let's not.</p>
        <p>When the United States was threatened by Germany, it built nuclear weapons to defend itself.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Let's not kid ourselves,'' you say (''Recipe for a Perfect Crisis,'' editorial, April 15). O.K., let's not.</p>
        <p>When the United States was threatened by Germany, it built nuclear weapons to defend itself.</p>
        <p>Now Iran is threatened by the United States. Do you expect Iran to invite the United States to tea and a nice talk?</p>
        <p>Tom Collier  Ann Arbor, Mich., April 15, 2006</p>
      </block>
